Goal: Understand regression concepts with examples

What is regression? Regression is a technique applied to estimate a continuous output variable as a function of one or more input variables.

What types of regression techniques exist? 1.Linear: \[y = a_0 + a_1*x_1 + a_2*x_2 + a_3*x_3 + \epsilon\] + Univariate + Multivariate 2. Polynomial: \[y = a_0 + a_1*x_1 + a_2*(x_1)^2 + a_3*(x_2) + a_4*(x_2)^2 + a_5*x_1*x_2 + \epsilon\] 3. Logistic: \[log(p_i/(1-p_i)) = a_0 + a_1*x_1 + a_2*x_2 + a_3*x_3 + \epsilon\]

Observation: cor < 0.2 means that the variation in response variable (Y) is not explained by the predictor variable. Here the correlation is ~80% which is good.

Build the model: function to be used lm. lm(formula,data)

LinearModelCars <- lm(formula = "dist~speed",data = cars)

Is the model good enough? Not known yet. It has to be statistically significant
